message.entry: The input message must have binary (0 or 1) values.
The {0} property must be a logical scalar.
To implement reflected data, the input length must be a multiple of 8.
The first element of a numeric vector Polynomial property must be 1.
A hex string that specifies the {0} property must begin with ''0x''.
The body of a hex string that specifies the {0} property must use the characters ''0123456789abcdefABCDEF'' only.
A hex {0} property must have the same length as the hex form of the Polynomial property.
A numeric vector that specifies the {0} property must have binary (0 or 1) values.
A numeric, nonscalar {0} property must be a row vector.
A numeric, nonscalar {0} property must have a length that is one less than the length of the numeric form of the Polynomial property.
